$ Python: enumerate
@ enumerate

`enumerate(sequence)` returns an iterator that provides → development/languages/Python/types/tuple[tuples] with two elements: the position of an element in the `sequence` (that is: the index) and the corresponding value:

gh|about-python|/builtin-functions/enumerate/demo.py||

{ Providing a start value

  When using `enumerate`, the index starts with 0 by default. It is possible to use the optional argument `start = n` to change the starting index:
  gh|about-python|/builtin-functions/enumerate/start-value.py||

